Signs of the end.
What indicates that Russia is coming out of the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest recession in 20 years.
According to analysts surveyed by Bloomberg, GDP of the Russian Federation shows positive dynamics - in the second quarter, GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This figure has been minimal since the beginning of 2015.
According to Rosstat, the decline in the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development also recently announced stabilization of the situation.
There is a slow growth ahead.
According to the CBI experts, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
“The index estimate of Russian GDP shows that the recession is behind and ahead is slow economic growth,” the Bank of Russia’s bulletin says.
The modular estimate of GDP for the current quarter has been increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter the decline in GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally-cleaned decline in GDP amounted to 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter the decline stopped: in April it amounted to 0.2%, and in May and June the change in GDP was within 0-0.15", - quotes the representative of the RIA Novosti.
The slowdown in the Russian economy over the past five quarters indicates that the bottom has passed.
Among other markers indicating signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls growth in demand for electricity and rail transport, revival of business.
If we make an amendment to the fact that the year is leap year, it is clear that the dynamics in the plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this the lower annual average temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight traffic, but it is difficult to get accurate data here, and plus-minus 0.5% of the half-yearly volume can also be explained by seasonality," explains Kirill Yakovenko of ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, lowering price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index stood at 7.2%, compared with 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, the last two weeks Rosstat has recorded deflation.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the exchange rate of the ruble, which, although showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, at the end of August since the beginning of the year strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy", - emphasizes Yakovenko.
In addition, since April, there has been an increase in the volume of industrial production in Russia.
In June, the figure increased by 1.7%.
The slowdown in foreign trade turnover from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
The positive trend is also demonstrated by the situation on the labour market, where the unemployment rate has fallen to 5.4%.
It was lower only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the prosperous situation on the labour market, the issue of real disposable income of the population is left to be desired.
In annual terms, the figure fell by 4.8 per cent.
This factor can hamper the recovery of the economy, as household spending contributes significantly to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy, their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, as risk factors for economic growth, we can also call the tough policy of the Bank of Russia.
The regulator keeps the rate at 10.5%, which does not best affect the real sector.
A negative factor is also the insufficiently high level of investment, which hinders the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year, the pace of the decline of the Russian economy will slow to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015", - says analyst Irina Rogova.
