The head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation Anton Wyno.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Wyno as the head of the administration of the President of Russia.
Earlier this position was held by Sergei Ivanov.
"The head of state by his decree appointed Anton Wyno as the head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation, freeing him from his position," the decree, signed by Putin and published on the Kremlin's website, reads.
Since May 2012, Wyno was deputy head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
Anton Eduardovich Vino was born on February 17, 1972 in Tallinn.
The father is Eduard Vino, Chairman of the Business Council of Cuba-Russia in the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice-President for External Relations and Cooperation with Shareholders of AvtoVAZ.
Grandfather Carl Wyno was from 1978 to 1988 the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001, he worked at the Russian Embassy in Japan, then in the Second Department of Asia of the Russian Foreign Ministry.
From 2002 to 2004, he held various positions in the Office of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 - Deputy Head of Protocol and Organizational Administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007 - the first deputy head of the protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008, Deputy Head of the Cabinet of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On April 25, 2008, he was appointed as the Head of the Protocol of the Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, Deputy Head of the Apparatus of the Government of the Russian Federation.
Since December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Apparatus of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012, he was appointed Deputy Head of the Administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
He speaks English and Japanese fluently.
Effective State Counsellor of the Russian Federation 1st class (class rank assigned by the Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of January 22, 2008)
Honorary certificate of the President of the Russian Federation (February 16, 2012) for his services in ensuring the activities of the Government of the Russian Federation and many years of good faith work.
