The largest M&A transaction has been launched in the pension market – KIT Finance Pension Administrator has launched the process of merging four controlled NPFs.
As a result, on the basis of "Gazfund Pension Savings" will be created NPF with a savings volume of about 373 billion rubles.
On the launch of the procedure of the merger of four pension funds - "KIT Finance", "PromagroFund", "Legacy" and "Gazfonds Pension Savings" - the owner of 100% of funds LLC "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" announced yesterday.
"The reorganization is carried out in coordination with the Central Bank, subject to the requirement of non-deterioration of the terms of the current contracts," the company said in a statement.
The association is carried out on the basis of "Gazfund Pension Savings".
As noted by the general director of this NPF, Oleg Bialoschitsky, the merger of funds allows to solve several problems: expansion of the geography of the presence, concentration of resources for development, reduction of costs, publication of best practices of each of the funds and optimization of corporate governance.
According to him, the approximate deadline for the completion of the consolidation is the second quarter of 2017.
As a result of the merger of the NPF "Gazfund Pension Savings" will become the largest player in the OPS market.
As of March 31, the amount of pension savings of the merging funds exceeded 373 billion rubles.
As can be seen from the reports on the website of the funds, the beneficiaries of their owner - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" - are currently Anatoly Gavrilenko (through the controlled LLC owns 65%) and NPF "Gazfund" (35%).
However, the group itself launched the group much later on competitors.
Thus, the controlled group of O1 NPF "Future" absorbed "Stalfonds" at the beginning of this year.
Currently, this combined NPF joins the Uralsib and Russian Standard funds.
"Combination into a single structure, in addition to reducing costs, is necessary to solve structural problems," said Nikolay Sidorov, Director General of the Future NPF.
Active work on the consolidation of funds has been going on since April and in the pension group "Safmar" - the NPF "European", "Education and Science" and "Regional Fund" should be merged into the NPF "Safmar" by the end of this year.
In 2017, the NPF "Doverie" will join them.
"The merger of funds will have the effect of strengthening control over risks, operating processes and costs," the Saffmar pension group said.
The pause in the pooling of funds, which was endured by "KIT Finance Pension Administrator", may be caused by several reasons, experts indicate.
Until recently, NPFs could not buy back more than 40% of the volume of infrastructure bonds issued, in which the group was actively located.
After the amendments to the Central Bank’s order in March this year for a number of issuers that meet the regulator’s requirements, such restrictions are no longer there.
If necessary, the entire issue can be redeemed by one major player", - says the director of the rating group of financial institutions Yuri Nogin.
Several of the top 15 asset managers of the NPF call the separation of spheres of influence and, as a result, staff appointments in a single fund, which should have been agreed by the group’s owners, another possible cause of the pause.
Yesterday, Anatoly Gavrilenko was not available for comment.
To the request of "U" in the NPF "Gazfond" were also not answered.
Although the consolidation of funds is a labor-intensive and inexpensive event, the long-distance decision will be justified.
As noted by the general director of the consulting company "Pension Partner" Sergey Okolesnov, the "Pension Savings Gazfond" has fewer outflows, the accession will allow to stabilize the base of other funds of the group.
At the same time, more successful experience of NPF "KIT Finance" and "Promagrofonda" in the construction of retail sales of OPS, as well as the use of more modern software will be required.
The requirements of the Central Bank for the processes and personnel of the NPF are constantly growing, so it is not advisable to duplicate the infrastructure on the four funds with a single investment policy, says Pavel Mitrofanov, Managing Director of Corporate Ratings "Expert RA".
"The effect of the reduction of duplicating functions will unambiguously overwhelm the possible costs of the combination," Mitrofanov said.
The cost of merging four funds Sergey Okolesnov estimates at 30-50 million rubles.
"The costs for the maintenance of four funds of this size amount to about 400 million rubles per year, with the consolidation in the medium term, the budget will actually be cut by half", - Mr. Okolesnov is sure.
